From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Crelia <crelia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] NeoForge Biome ClimateSettings Getter

Adds getModifiedClimateSettings() and getModifiedSpecialEffects() methods
to net.minecraft.world.level.biome.Biome. These are simple getter wrappers
that the NeoForge coremod ReplaceFieldWithGetterAccess targets to replace
direct GETFIELD accesses with virtual method calls, enabling biome modification.

At runtime, NeoForge's real ModifiableBiomeInfo replaces these simple getters.
For compile time, these return the backing fields directly.

diff --git a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/biome/Biome.java b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/biome/Biome.java
index 90c165c890a2d998e3b0af9b4310e3995ede6f64..aaaa0000aaaa0000aaaa0000aaaa0000aaaa00 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/biome/Biome.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/world/level/biome/Biome.java
@@ -92,6 +92,24 @@
         return this.mobSettings;
     }
 
+    // NeoForge start - modifiable biome accessors (compile-time stubs)
+    /**
+     * Returns the (possibly modified) climate settings for this biome.
+     * NeoForge's coremod replaces direct field access to climateSettings with this method.
+     */
+    public ClimateSettings getModifiedClimateSettings() {
+        return this.climateSettings;
+    }
+
+    /**
+     * Returns the (possibly modified) special effects for this biome.
+     * NeoForge's coremod replaces direct field access to specialEffects with this method.
+     */
+    public BiomeSpecialEffects getModifiedSpecialEffects() {
+        return this.specialEffects;
+    }
+    // NeoForge end
+
     public boolean hasPrecipitation() {
         return this.climateSettings.hasPrecipitation();
     }
